01:01:28.580 --> 01:01:32.580
Well, the factory had all the machines shut off.

01:01:32.580 --> 01:01:39.580
And one time, Marlene Elbert, she passed away now, she lived in Ayriford.

01:01:39.580 --> 01:01:43.580
And she wrote, I love Elvis, down the trouser leg.

01:01:43.580 --> 01:01:46.580
So all the machines went off now.

01:01:46.580 --> 01:01:48.580
So we said, what's the matter, what's the matter?

01:01:48.580 --> 01:01:53.580
Well, if you don't own her, you'll all be sacked off the line.

01:01:53.580 --> 01:01:57.580
Well, she was Elvis mad.

01:01:57.580 --> 01:02:01.580
Elvis, she was crackers, she had all Elvis all over her machine.

01:02:01.580 --> 01:02:06.580
And she said to the supervisor, she said it was me.

01:02:06.580 --> 01:02:08.580
She said it was me.

01:02:08.580 --> 01:02:10.580
She said it was me.

01:02:10.580 --> 01:02:17.580
And she had to go up the office, and I think she had to pay for the trouser.

01:02:17.580 --> 01:02:21.580
But it was only chalk, I love Elvis, all the way down the leg.

01:02:21.580 --> 01:02:23.580
She wasn't sacked then?

01:02:23.580 --> 01:02:28.580
No. She had a warning, and they said that you mustn't do things like that.

01:02:28.580 --> 01:02:30.580
But they didn't sack her.

01:02:32.580 --> 01:02:34.580
Great.

